headline: PFG Q3 Deep Dive: Diversified Segments Drive Growth Despite Margin Pressures
summary: Financial services company Principal Financial Group (NASDAQGS:PFG) fell short of the markets revenue expectations in Q3 CY2025, but sales rose 6.1% year on year to $3.90 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $2.10 per share was 4.5% below analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: Principal Financial Group (PFG): Assessing Valuation After Dividend Increase and Upbeat Outlook Despite Q3 Earnings Miss
summary: Principal Financial Group (PFG) announced an 8% increase to its quarterly dividend after releasing third-quarter earnings that missed Wall Street expectations. Management reiterated confidence in full-year targets and highlighted steady operational momentum. See our latest analysis for Principal Financial Group.
